CITY COURT OF NEW YORK

GENERAL TERM,

MAY, 1893. Starr Cash Car Co. v. Reinhardt. Joseph O. Bosenbamm, for defendant (appellant). Ja/neway, Thatcher d Bieha/rds, for plaintiffs (respondents). Fitzsimons, J.

The trial fee allowed for the so-called trial on November 6, 1891, should not have been allowed, and the *626order appealed from is modified to the extent of disallowing said charge, and to that amount the bill of costs taxed is reduced, and as so modified the order appealed from is affirmed, without costs.

Ehrlich, Oh. J., concurs.

Ordered accordingly.
